title: Number of oncology practices in the U.S. by region and size 2013
summary: This grouped bar chart shows Number of new patients on the Y-axis for 4 different Countrys for 3 groups 1-2 physicians, 3-6 physicians, and 7 or more physicians that are presented on the X-axis.
Out of all 3 groups, 7 or more physicians had the highest Number of new patients in Country South and 1-2 physicians had the lowest Number of new patients in Country West.
Among all the Countrys, 3-6 physicians had the highest Number of new patients in Country West and lowest Number of new patients in Country South.
There is a gap of 17.0 between the highest and lowest Number of new patients found for 3-6 physicians in Country West and South.

max_summary: This grouped bar chart shows Number of new patients on the Y-axis for 4 different Countrys for 3 groups 1-2 physicians, 3-6 physicians, and 7 or more physicians that are presented on the X-axis.
In Country South, 7 or more physicians had the highest Number of new patients 75.0 among the 3 groups and in West, 1-2 physicians had the lowest Number of new patients 24.0.
Among all the Countrys, 3-6 physicians had the highest Number of new patients 46.0 in Country West and lowest value 29.0 in Country South.
There is a gap of 17.0 between the highest and lowest Number of new patients found for 3-6 physicians in Country West and South.
Out of all 3 groups, the highest gap between the maximum and minimum Number of new patients was found in case of 1-2 physicians.

7 or more physicians had the maximum Number of new patients out of all 3 groups in Country South followed by 7 or more physicians in South, and the minimum Number of new patients is found for 1-2 physicians in West.

On average, the Country South had the highest Number of new patients for all 3 groups 1-2 physicians, 3-6 physicians, and 7 or more physicians. Whereas Northeast had the lowest average Number of new patients.
